# BANCO Store — environment variable NAMES only (no secrets).
# Copy the platform-specific template and fill values in your secret store.
#
# Replit: use the encrypted secret store + public keys in .replit (see replit.md).
# AWS:    deploy/aws/env/.env.production.example
# GCP:    deploy/gcp/env/.env.production.example
# Staging smoke checklist: audit/production-readiness/STAGING-REQUIRED-SECRETS.md
#
# Core (API will not boot without PORT + DATABASE_URL):
#   PORT DATABASE_URL SESSION_SECRET PAYMENT_CONFIG_ENCRYPTION_KEY
# Auth:
#   CLERK_SECRET_KEY CLERK_PUBLISHABLE_KEY
# Optional features:
#   RESEND_API_KEY OPENAI_API_KEY OPENAI_MODEL OPENAI_TIMEOUT_MS OPENAI_MAX_RETRIES
#   OPENAI_MAX_COMPLETION_TOKENS ERROR_ALERT_WEBHOOK PAYMOB_* OBJECT_STORAGE_*
# Mobile / EAS (public, baked at build):
#   EXPO_PUBLIC_DOMAIN EXPO_PUBLIC_CLERK_PUBLISHABLE_KEY EXPO_PUBLIC_ROUTER_ORIGIN
#
# NEVER commit .env files with real values.
